ce:section.ce:para:
The feasibility of using B-CDs for TET detection was verified through spiked recovery experiments. Tap water from the laboratory was selected as the sample matrix, and spiked recovery tests were conducted with TET at various concentrations. Each sample was measured in parallel six times, and the results are summarized in Table 1
                        . The recovery rates ranged from 100 % to 105 %, with relative standard deviations (RSDs) below 2 %, indicating good precision and accuracy of the method. The limit of detection (LOD) for B-CDs was calculated using the formula LOD = 3σ/K, where σ represents the standard deviation of blank B-CDs and K denotes the slope of the standard curve. The calculated LOD for B-CDs was 0.033 μmol·L⁻¹. Compared with previously reported literature on TET detection using fluorescent CDs (see Table 2
                        ), the LOD achieved in this study is lower than most reported values, demonstrating higher sensitivity in TET detection and significant implications for trace TET analysis.
